[{"client_msg_id":"fac9a924-04a0-4a16-975b-83cbddff4fdb","type":"message","text":"so in Pandas slicing includes extrema?  how is that not confusing? :smirk:","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616762615.048300","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"QfbSM","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"so in Pandas slicing includes extrema?  how is that not confusing? "},{"type":"emoji","name":"smirk"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616762615.048300","reply_count":12,"reply_users_count":3,"latest_reply":"1616765120.051900","reply_users":["UPSSPPBFV","U6740K1SP","UDB26738Q"],"is_locked":false,"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"9ca97a0b-452b-46de-a78c-8ca99c9ca819","type":"message","text":"It's actually more complicated than that, and even more confusing if you're not careful:\n\n• slicing series with just `[]`is just like Numpy, i.e. upper bound excluded;\n• slicing dataframes by position using `.iloc[]` is like Numpy, i.e. upper bound excluded;\n• slicing dataframes by label using `.loc[]` is with upper bound _included_, even if the labels are integers (which is probably what confuses people most. You need to have a real grasp of row positions vs. row labels).\nThings get hairy when you combine slicing by label with slicing by position, or include conditions or masks in the mix. Luckily I don't need to use slices often...","user":"UPSSPPBFV","ts":"1616764765.049300","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"f=nIO","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"It's actually more complicated than that, and even more confusing if you're not careful:\n\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_list","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"slicing series with just "},{"type":"text","text":"[]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"is just like Numpy, i.e. upper bound excluded;"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"slicing dataframes by position using "},{"type":"text","text":".iloc[]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is like Numpy, i.e. upper bound excluded;"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"slicing dataframes by label using "},{"type":"text","text":".loc[]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is with upper bound "},{"type":"text","text":"included","style":{"italic":true}},{"type":"text","text":", even if the labels are integers (which is probably what confuses people most. You need to have a real grasp of row positions vs. row labels)."}]}],"style":"bullet","indent":0},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"\nThings get hairy when you combine slicing by label with slicing by position, or include conditions or masks in the mix. Luckily I don't need to use slices often..."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616762615.048300","parent_user_id":"UDB26738Q"},{"client_msg_id":"12bf1e0b-f27e-4288-ac18-9ecf3ba13bb5","type":"message","text":"at least they got rid of the mixed version (the old `ix[]`)","user":"U6740K1SP","ts":"1616764839.049500","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"U6740K1SP","ts":"1616764958.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"BlX7","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"at least they got rid of the mixed version (the old "},{"type":"text","text":"ix[]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616762615.048300","parent_user_id":"UDB26738Q"},{"client_msg_id":"11b414dd-e0fb-4e2b-a2ef-ac80a8c08af5","type":"message","text":"yeah, I'm getting more and more confused","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616764846.049700","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"qdYV","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"yeah, I'm getting more and more confused"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616762615.048300","parent_user_id":"UDB26738Q"},{"client_msg_id":"c32a4873-fe1d-4cee-be45-b2f0a17ac507","type":"message","text":"The thing that confuses people most is that if your dataframe has integer row labels starting at 0, `df.iloc[0:10, :]`will contain one fewer rows than `df.loc[0:10, :]`:stuck_out_tongue:.","user":"UPSSPPBFV","ts":"1616764896.049900","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"UPSSPPBFV","ts":"1616764935.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"ZpL","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The thing that confuses people most is that if your dataframe has integer row labels starting at 0, "},{"type":"text","text":"df.iloc[0:10, :]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"will contain one fewer rows than "},{"type":"text","text":"df.loc[0:10, :]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"emoji","name":"stuck_out_tongue"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616762615.048300","parent_user_id":"UDB26738Q"},{"client_msg_id":"3f6d7e1e-edbe-428f-a7ae-2f8f9a7e7d8c","type":"message","text":"also, people here don't remember whether methods are of pandas or of the dataframe object","user":"UDB26738Q","ts":"1616764957.050200","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"rhJ","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"also, people here don't remember whether methods are of pandas or of the dataframe object"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1616762615.048300","parent_user_id":"UDB26738Q"},{"client_msg_id":"beb521f5-acc0-44d3-9cfb-3ed521518b65","type":"message","text":"Yeah, I'm lucky that when I started using Pandas, `.loc[]` and `.iloc[]` had already been implemented, so I didn't have to learn the older method :stuck_out_tongue:.","user":"UPSSPPBFV","ts":"1616764982.050500","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"OFz","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Yeah, I'm lucky that when I started using Pandas, "},{"type":"text","text":".loc[]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","text":".iloc[]","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text